festival.introText:
Lets Love Life Charity Festival 2023.

 

Over 40 DJs across 4 stages - Dancing in the Woods

reviews.title: Review of Lets Love Life 2022
reviews.body: brilliant local event that supports charity with a fun filled day of music and dancing. great food choices too and onsite parking (but download ticket before go as weak signal there)

reviews.title: Review of Lets Love Life 2022
reviews.body: Absolutely amazing. Roger played an amazing set (as always) and the atmosphere was legendary. Will be in attendance next year!!!!

reviews.title: Review of Lets Love Life 2022
reviews.body: SUAT didn't turn up...other than that awesome

reviews.title: Review of Lets Love Life 2022
reviews.body: What a find! it was like being transported back in time.....in the middle.of the woods in Aldershot. great atmosphere, amazing tunes....only drawback was the amount of dust by the main stage. What you pay for dancing in the woods I guess ?

faqs.question: When is Lets Love Life 2023?
faqs.answer: Lets Love Life takes place on Saturday 27th May 2023.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is Lets Love Life?
faqs.answer: Lets Love Life is held at the Rushmoor Arena, Aldershot, Hampshire.

faqs.question: Does Lets Love Life have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Lets Love Life. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Does Lets Love Life have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Lets Love Life is a non-camping festival so camping equipment is not needed.

location.address: rushmoor arena, rushmoor road, aldershot, near london
